A 2-step wizard modal component:
- Props: isOpen, onClose, onComplete (called after step 2 done or skipped)
- Step indicator at top: "① Ingredient Details  →  ② Initial Stock"
  Step 1 label bold/dark when on step 1, gray when on step 2
  Step 2 label bold/dark when on step 2, gray when on step 1

STEP 1 UI — fields:
  * Name (text input, required, placeholder: "e.g. Chicken Breast")
  * Unit (select: piece, kg, g, L, ml, bottle, can, pack, box, bag)
  * Cost per unit (number input, min 0, label: "Cost / Unit (฿)")
  * Low stock threshold (number input, min 0, label: "Alert when below")
  Footer buttons: Cancel | Save & Continue →

STEP 2 UI — fields:
  * Quantity (number input, min 0, required)
  * Expiry date (date input, optional, label: "Expiry Date (optional)")
  Footer buttons: ← Back | Skip | Add Stock

Logic:
- On "Save & Continue": validate name not empty, call POST /api/ingredients
  with { name, unit, price_per_unit, low_stock_threshold }
  Store returned ingredient _id in state, advance to step 2
- On "Add Stock": validate quantity > 0, call POST /api/ingredients/:id/stock
